President Obama spoke with Prime Minister Netanyahu to reaffirm his commitment to Israel's security. He emphasized that no country should tolerate rocket attacks against civilians. The President appreciated the Prime Minister's collaboration with the new Egyptian government to achieve a sustainable ceasefire and a long-term solution. He commended the Prime Minister for accepting the Egyptian ceasefire proposal, while also asserting Israel's right to self-defense. The President stated that the US would use the ceasefire opportunity to enhance efforts in assisting Israel with its security needs, particularly addressing the smuggling of weapons into Gaza. He expressed his dedication to securing additional funding for missile defense programs like Iron Dome.